s not\nexpected in a resonance of the bar, supporting previous hypothesis of\nincomplete vertical phase-mixing. When we apply the same methodology to\nsimulations of barred galaxies, we extract substructures corresponding to the\nOuter Linbdlad and the 1:1 Resonances and observe patterns consistent with the\ndata. This data-driven characterization allows for a quantitative comparison\nwith models, providing a key tool to comprehend the dynamics of the Milky Way.\n(Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Jun 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 09:09:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-16"}
