s define a separate locus in SFR_FUV,\nSFR_Ha space with respect to the LTGs, which is well represented by the\nrelation log (SFR_FUV.CaF2) = 0.70xlog (SFR_{Ha})-1.26.The disk structure of\nthe FUV.CaF2 emitting populations discovered in all the ETGs implies\ndissipative processes and wet merging events. The systematic discrepancy\nbetween SFRs derived from Ha and FUV fluxes suggests that rejuvenation episodes\nin ETGs cannot sustain constant SF over ~100 Myrs timescales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Jun 2022 14:00:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
